29/09/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- Minister of Health Nikitas Kaklamanis and Turkish counterpart Recep Akdag sealed a bilateral agreement Wednesday (28 September) on co-operation in the health sector. It provides for enhanced collaboration in a number of medical fields, from major disasters to organ transplants. The agreement was described as another important step in establishing good neighbourly relations between Greece and Turkey. (Kathimerini - 29/09/05) 
